<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ransom1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ransom,</orth> subst. 1) price paid for the redemption of a prisoner; in a proper and a metaphorical sense: <bibl n="shak. ven 550" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 550</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.111" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.121" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 121</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.1.74" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 74</bibl> (<emph>O r., r.!</emph>). <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 56</bibl> (<emph>the world's r., blessed Mary's son;</emph> cf. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 16</bibl>). <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.141" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.141" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 141</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.57" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.96" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.5.60" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 5, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.5.60" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 5, 60</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.133" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.133" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 133</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 80</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 80</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 80</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.4.11" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.4.11" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 11</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.5.9" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.72" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.72" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 72</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.148" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 148</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.148" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 148</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.72" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 73</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 73</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 73</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.297" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 297</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 10</bibl> (<emph>make their r.,</emph> == pay). <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.7.40" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 7, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 105</bibl> (== a sum paid to deliver a prisoner for debt). <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 94</bibl> (<emph>--s</emph>). <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 196</bibl>.<lb />2) atonement, expiation: <cit><quote>if hearty sorrow be a sufficient r. for offence,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 75</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>lowly words were r. for their fault,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.127" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 127</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.265" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 265</bibl>* <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 3, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.80" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 80</bibl>.

